    <!-- Application Structure Plan: The SPA is designed around a central, tab-based navigation allowing users to switch between three distinct exploration modes: (1) A "Timeline Explorer" for chronological discovery, (2) a "Comparative Framework" for thematic analysis, (3) a "Defining Divinity" section for terminological clarity, and (4) a "Tradition Deep Dive" for detailed reading. This structure was chosen to deconstruct the dense report into user-driven discovery paths. The timeline provides historical context, the comparison view facilitates analytical understanding, the definitions section clarifies core concepts, and the deep dive offers detailed information on demand. This non-linear approach is superior to a simple scroll-through of the report, as it empowers users to focus on the aspects most interesting to them, fostering engagement and better comprehension of the complex, interconnected material. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: 
        - Timeline: (Report Info: Section 8 Dates -> Goal: Show Change/Chronology -> Viz: Chart.js Scatter Plot -> Interaction: Click point to load details -> Justification: Visually represents historical emergence and overlap, more engaging than a static list. -> Library: Chart.js).
        - Comparative Framework: (Report Info: Section 7 Table -> Goal: Compare -> Viz: Interactive HTML/CSS Cards -> Interaction: Click filter buttons to re-sort/highlight cards by theme -> Justification: Allows dynamic, multi-faceted comparison beyond a static table. -> Method: JS/Tailwind).
        - Defining Divinity: (Report Info: All sections -> Goal: Organize/Clarify -> Viz: Styled text blocks in a grid -> Interaction: Static text -> Justification: Centralizes key term definitions for easy reference and comparison. -> Method: Tailwind).
        - Deep Dive Sections: (Report Info: Sections 1-6 -> Goal: Inform -> Viz: Dynamically populated text blocks -> Interaction: Content loads based on clicks from timeline or cards -> Justification: Presents detailed info without overwhelming the initial view. -> Method: JS/HTML).
        - Conceptual Diagrams (e.g., Theurgy, Neidan): (Report Info: Textual descriptions -> Goal: Organize/Explain -> Viz: Styled HTML/CSS Flexbox/Grid layouts -> Interaction: Static visual aid -> Justification: Simple, clear representation of concepts without external graphics. -> Method: Tailwind).
    -->
