                            <p class="mb-2">Theurgy operates on the principle that the material world is not evil, but is the final stage of divine emanation. It is filled with <strong>sunthemata</strong>, or divine "signatures," embedded in specific plants, stones, and sounds. The theurgist uses these material symbols as sympathetic links to attract and commune with the corresponding divine power.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div>
                            <h4 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">The Rituals of Union</h4>
                            <p class="mb-2">Theurgic rituals were designed to purify the soul and elevate it. Rites of Invitation (<strong>telestics</strong>) aimed to draw a divine presence into the material world, such as animating a statue. Rites of Elevation (<strong>anagoge</strong>) focused on the ascent of the practitioner's own soul through the cosmic spheres to achieve <strong>henosis</strong>, or mystical union.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                `
            },
            "taoism": {
                id: "taoism",
                name: "Taoist Internal Alchemy",
                period: "c. 618-907 CE",
                start: 618,
                goal: "Creation of an immortal spiritual body (Xian); return to the Tao.",
                method: "Internal psycho-physiological alchemy (refining Jing, Qi, Shen).",
                worldview: "A laboratory for internal transformation.",
                content: `
                    <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Taoist Neidan: Forging the Immortal Self</h3>
                    <p class="mb-4">The ultimate goal of Taoist esoteric practice is to become a <strong>Xian</strong>, an immortal being. This pursuit shifted from early, dangerous External Alchemy (Waidan) to <strong>Neidan</strong> (Internal Alchemy), where the practitioner's own body becomes the alchemical laboratory for creating a refined, immortal spiritual body.</p>
                    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
                        <div>
                            <h4 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">The Three Treasures</h4>
                            <p class="mb-2">The raw materials for this inner work are the "Three Treasures" inherent in every human being: <strong>Jing</strong> (generative essence), <strong>Qi</strong> (vital energy/breath), and <strong>Shen</strong> (spirit/consciousness). The process is a sequential, psycho-physiological transformation through meditation, breath control, and lifestyle moderation.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="flex flex-col items-center justify-center p-4 bg-[#FDF6E3] rounded-lg">
                            <h4 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">The Alchemical Process</h4>
                            <div class="text-center font-semibold">
                                <div class="p-2">Jing (Essence)</div>
                                <div class="text-2xl transform rotate-90">➔</div>
                                <div class="p-2">Qi (Vital Energy)</div>
                                <div class="text-2xl transform rotate-90">➔</div>
                                <div class="p-2">Shen (Spirit)</div>
